## How to grow this

- **Lazily, during grilling.** When a fuzzy or overloaded term surfaces while
  stress-testing a plan, pin its single canonical word here the moment the decision
  crystallises — not in a later documentation pass.
- **One concept, one word.** When several words name the same thing, choose one and
  push the rest to `_Avoid_`. When one word names several things, split it into distinct
  terms.
- **Keep definitions tight.** One or two sentences. Define what it IS; cross-reference
  the entities it relates to or is distinct from.
- **Domain terms only.** Concepts unique to this project belong; general programming
  vocabulary (timeouts, retries, error types) does not, even if used heavily.
- **Group with subheadings** when natural clusters emerge; a flat list is fine when all
  terms belong to one cohesive area.
- **Multiple bounded contexts?** Add a `CONTEXT-MAP.md` at the repo root listing each
  context, where its `CONTEXT.md` lives, and how the contexts relate.
